problem:
In right triangle $ABC$, shown below, $\cos{C}=\frac{9\sqrt{130}}{130}$.  Find $AC$.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(7,0)--(0,9)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw(rightanglemark((7,0),(0,0),(0,9),20),black+linewidth(1));
label("$A$",(0,0),W);
label("$B$",(7,0),E);
label("$C$",(0,9),W);
label("$\sqrt{130}$",(7,0)--(0,9),NE);
[/asy]
